description:
I dont think the people of Grailed are ready for this one. Yes you read the title correctly, these are mittens made of real Brown Bear fur and leather. Insane.
Here’s what I know about them.
- I bought these at an estate sale. The owners said they found them in their father’s basement wrapped in newspaper from the late 1940s.
- These could be as old as the 1900s
- These were used for snowmobiling, as they smelled of fuel when I first bought them. It also explains the wear around where the break would be.
I gave these a bit of a cleaning and left them outside for a bit. They still smell like fuel. It reminds me of my grandfather lol.
I have big hands and these fit with still some room. Kind of a one size fits all thing.
Measurements:
- just under 14 inches tall
- opening is bout 9 inches across
- Leather palm is about 6.2 inches tall
Otherwise, this comes as shown. Super unique piece. True piece of Canadian history. Anywhere from 1900s to 1940s. To be cherished.

84 on the sleeve refers to the player’s number. “Paul” is chain stitched on the front. “Spartans” lettering patches on the back.

Grailed-core Prada sunglasses. These seemingly became incredibly sought over this passed year and Id wager they will become even more in th next. I guarantee youll see some album cover with these on it.
From the Mid 2000s. Some people call the metal side detailing a “flame”, “wave” or “tribal”.
This version is rimless with oversized lenses. I know the smaller versions of these released in 2005. I think these are from 04 or 06.
The lenses are pretty fucking murked on these and frame has wear too. They are missing bose pads, but Id be happy to get replaced for you for no extra cost. Basically these are beaters and are priced accordingly.
2000s Prada Oversized Flame Wraps
Made in Italy
